  "instructions": [
    "Heat the coconut oil in a large pan over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the pork shoulder and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the star anise, shio-koji, and Thai red curry paste, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Pour in the coconut milk and bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 20 minutes, or until the pork is tender.",
    "Stir in the fish sauce and brown sugar.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve the curry hot, garnished with chopped Thai basil, on a hot stone plate."
